         <abstract>
            <p>Determining an optimal capital structure requires that the risk of insolvency associated with debt be taken into account explicitly. In valuing a capital project, the cost imputed to this insolvency risk should be deducted from the tax benefits of the debt capacity contributed by the project. This paper incorporates these considerations in valuation procedures for capital budgeting decisions.</p>
